<AUTHOR>zulu45</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>I own a 2008 Patriot 4WD. It is not the trail-rated version, but has the CVT2. Since purchasing it, I have had it during two ice storms, one in early 2008, and the horrific one here in Kentucky in 2009. And during both storms, there was one constant: this Jeep just can't get stuck! No matter where I was driving, even without being the trail-rated version, it handled everything, including hills that full-sized trucks with off-road packages couldn't even come close to handling. The fuel economy is great, but it's not sluggish. Acceleration is great, and the auto-stick is a lot of fun, and helps with city MPGs. The interior isn't luxurious, but it's a great utility interior.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Cherokee styling, comfortable seats, 4WD mode is amazing, acceleration is great, and the standard stock speakers are quite nice. I manage to get 30MPG highway. The CVT, once used to it, offers so much control to control acceleration.</FAVORITE>
